      "writtenOn": "2026-04-13T23:22:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`RefDirectory.Trait` is internal, so I don\u0027t think we should use it in a public API signature. Probably easiest to fix by moving it out of internal, but... is it ever valid to not pass `SORTED` as a trait? The constructors for this class ensure the refs are always sorted. It\u0027s actually confusing for a caller like `org.eclipse.jgit.pgm/src/org/eclipse/jgit/pgm/debug/RebuildCommitGraph.java` to specify `SORTED` because there\u0027s nothing obvious in the caller doing the sorting.\n\nYou could rename this as `additionalTraits`, but then callers have to know or look up which traits are already included. You could also make it specific to `PEELED`, but that feels short-sighted (presumably we\u0027ll have `fully-peeled` too eventually?). Maybe someone else has an idea.\n\nIt\u0027s also strange that we\u0027re giving this information separately from the refs. Why not add it to the constructors or create a dedicated setter (`addTraits()`) for it? If you don\u0027t want to break the API, you could add duplicates of the constructors and deprecate the existing ones.",
      "revId": "2df51c59c4b9dfbba5724eeeb5c7f4f2bdb79c77",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
